Zulum ta rattaba hannu kan yarjejeniya da jami'ar Al-Azhar don ci gaban Borno.
Gwamnatin jihar Borno a Najeriya ta rattaba hannu kan yarjejeniya da wasu jami'o'in Masar don bunkasa ayyukan kiwon lafiya a jihar da kuma horar da dalibai.
An yi wannan yarjejeniya ne a lokacin ziyarar da gwamnan jihar, Farfesa Babagana Umaru Zulum, ya kai birnin Alkahira, Masar, inda ya ziyarci kungiyar tsofaffin daliban jami'ar Al-Azhar a ranar Laraba.
Gwamna Zulum ya bayyana bukatar hadin gwiwa wajen horar da malamai a makarantun sakandaren jihar Borno da kuma masu wa'azi.
Gwamnan ya kuma yi kira da a bude cibiyar Al-Azhar a Maiduguri, hedkwatar jihar, wato sashen koyar da harshen Larabci da kuma kafa reshe na kungiyar tsofaffin ɗaliban Al-Azhar a jihar.
Zulum ya kuma ziyarci Jami'ar Ain Shams, a Alkahira, inda ya gana da Shugaban Jami'ar. Sun tattauna batutuwa da dama da suka shafi hadin gwiwa da Jami'ar da jihar Borno a fannonin bincike na likitanci, a kokarin da take na kafa asibitin koyarwa na Jami'ar Jihar Borno.
Farfesa Babagana Zulum ya tattauna yiwuwar tura daliban likitanci zuwa Masar don darussan daban-daban da za su samar da damar samun kwarewa a fannoni daban-daban na kiwon lafiya.
Bayan ganawar ta sirri, an bai wa gwamnan rangadin sashen koyar da likitoci da na kimiyya na jami'ar, inda aka yi masa cikakken bayani kan tsare-tsaren da aka gabatar. Farfesa Zulum ya gamsu da wadannan kuma yana fatan karfafa shirinsa na inganta Jami'ar Jihar Borno.
Khartoum: Pompeo da Hamdok sun gana.
Firayim Ministan Sudan Abdallah Hamdok ya sanar da jerin tarurruka kan muhimman batutuwa tare da Sakataren Harkokin Wajen Amurka Mike Pompeo a Khartoum, gami da cire Sudan daga jerin kasashen da Washington ta sanya a matsayin masu daukar nauyin 'yan ta'adda.
